Detection and Response Detect if a machine in your system has been compromised by following all of these steps: The malware creates files in the following directories: /usr/local/sbin /usr/local/bin /usr/bin /usr/libexec /tmp Check if there are suspicious files in these locations
Run the following command to get the PID: netstat -ltnp | grep -w ‘:61131’ and then: sudo kill -9 <PID> to kill the process
Use the command: netstat -tupln Response: Find the PID of the process and kill it

The shared object was written to /usr/local/lib/systemhealt.so by the setup script and directives were added to /etc/ld.so.preload to allow the shared object to be loaded with every file that is executed
